using System;

namespace UniqueCharacters
{
    class Program
    {
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            string[] lines = System.IO.File.ReadAllLines(@"C:\input.txt");
            int count = 0;

            foreach (string line in lines)
            {
                bool isUnique = true;

                for (int i = 0; i < line.Length - 1; i++)
                {
                    for (int j = i + 1; j < line.Length; j++)
                    {
                        if (line[i] == line[j])
                        {
                            isUnique = false;
                            break;
                        }
                    }
                    if (!isUnique)
                    {
                        break;
                    }
                }
                if (isUnique)
                {
                    count++;
                }
            }
            Console.WriteLine("Number of lines with unique characters: " + count);
        }
    }
}

Here is the code in C# that outputs the unclosed brackets in the given string:

```csharp
using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        string s = "(){}[])))(((()))[][][]{}{}{}{()(){}}{}{([][{)})"; // the given string

        Stack<int> stack = new Stack<int>();
        for (int i = 0; i < s.Length; i++)
        {
            char c = s[i];
            if (c == '(' || c == '{' || c == '[')
            {
                stack.Push(i);
            }
            else if (c == ')' || c == '}' || c == ']')
            {
                if (stack.Count == 0)
                {
                    Console.WriteLine("Unexpected closing bracket at position " + i);
                }
                else
                {
                    int start = stack.Pop();
                    if (c == ')' && s[start] != '(' ||
                        c == '}' && s[start] != '{' ||
                        c == ']' && s[start] != '[')
                    {
                        Console.WriteLine("Mismatched brackets at positions " + start + " and " + i);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        while (stack.Count > 0)
        {
            Console.WriteLine("Unclosed bracket at position " + stack.Pop());
        }
    }
}
```

This program uses a stack to keep track of the positions of opening brackets. When a closing bracket is encountered, it pops the last position from the stack and checks if the brackets match. If there is a mismatch, it reports the positions of the mismatched brackets. If there are still brackets on the stack after iterating through the string, it reports their positions as unclosed brackets.

可以使用操作文件的代码库（如`fs`模块或更高级别的`fs-extra`模块），以编程方式读取包含关键字的文件，并删除包含关键字的指定行。

要删除指定的行，可以分成两个步骤：

1. 读取文件内容到数组中。
2. 找到包含关键字的行，并从数组中删除这些行。
3. 将更新后的数组重新写入文件中。

以下是一个可能的实现：

```javascript
const fs = require('fs');
const readline = require('readline');
const rl = readline.createInterface({
    input: fs.createReadStream('exampleFile.txt'),
});

const keyword = 'example';   // 要删除包含此关键字的行
const lines = [];

// 逐行读取文件
rl.on('line', (line) => {
    if (line.indexOf(keyword) === -1) {   // 关键字不包含在行中
        lines.push(line);   // 将行添加到数组中
    }
});

// 读取文件结束
rl.on('close', () => {
    // 将更新后的内容写入文件中
    const updatedContent = lines.join('\n');
    fs.writeFileSync('exampleFile.txt', updatedContent);
});
```

请注意，此实现假定文件中的所有行都以换行符`\n`结尾。如果文件中的某些行以其他换行符（如`\r\n`）结尾，则需要进行一些修改。

